  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 3,
      1867, p. 691-2: "Sacadas, of Argos, one of the most eminent of the Greek musicians....In the
      time of Sacadas most of the musicians were poets also...The kind of poetry which these masters
      cultivated was chiefly, if not exclusively, the elegy....."</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Sacadas, Poet and famous aulos player from Argos. He
      participated in the second organisation (kat&#xE1;stasis) of music in Sparta (Plut. Mor. 1134bc)
      ... S. also wrote elegiac verses ....." Harmon, Roger (Basel). "Sacadas." Brill's New Pauly.
      Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online.
      Tufts University Library. 02 December 2009 </mads:note>
